Interface YggdrasilSerializable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    YggdrasilSerializable.YggdrasilExtendedSerializable, YggdrasilSerializable.YggdrasilRobustSerializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Color, CreeperData, Date, Direction, DroppedItemData, EnchantmentType, EndermanData, EntityData, EntityType, Experience, FallingBlockData, GriefPreventionHook.GriefPreventionRegion, GuardianData, HorseData, ItemData, ItemType, MinecartData, OcelotData, PigData, PlayerData, RabbitData, Region, SheepData, SimpleEntityData, SkeletonData, ThrownPotionData, Time, Timeperiod, Timespan, VillagerData, VisualEffect, WolfData, WorldGuardHook.WorldGuardRegion, XpOrbData

    public interface YggdrasilSerializable
    Marks a class as serialisable by Yggdrasil.

    Enums don't have to implement this interface to be serialisable, but can implement YggdrasilSerializable.YggdrasilRobustEnum.

    Author:

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  YggdrasilSerializable.YggdrasilExtendedSerializable
      A class that has transient fields or more generally wants to exactly define which fields to write to/read from stream should implement this interface.
      static interface  YggdrasilSerializable.YggdrasilRobustEnum
      Provides a method to resolve missing enum constants.
      static interface  YggdrasilSerializable.YggdrasilRobustSerializable
      A class that has had fields added, changed, or removed from it should implement this interface to handle the now invalid/missing fields that may still be read from stream.
